  "prompt": "Where are Samsung phones made?",
  "response": "Samsung phones are manufactured in several locations around the world, reflecting the company's global reach and diversified production strategy. Key production sites include:\n\n1. **South Korea:** This is where Samsung's headquarters are located, and it is a crucial site for the production of high-end devices and R&D.\n\n2. **Vietnam:** Samsung has significant manufacturing facilities in Vietnam, which produce a large portion of their smartphones. The company has invested heavily in these facilities to expand their production capacity.\n\n3. **India:** Samsung has a large manufacturing plant in Noida, India. It is one of the largest mobile phone manufacturing facilities in the world.\n\n4. **China:** While Samsung has reduced its manufacturing footprint in China in recent years, it still has some production there.\n\n5. **Brazil:** Samsung also has a production facility in Manaus, Brazil, serving the Latin American market.\n\nThese diverse locations help Samsung manage production costs and logistics, as well as respond to regional market demands effectively.",
